      "author": "RobertttBS",
      "description": "fix: patch canvas prototype after layout is ready to fix pinned tab race on Windows\r\nOn Windows with a pinned Canvas tab, canvasView.canvas is not yet\r\ninitialized when the plugin patches the Canvas prototype during onload().\r\nThe fallback event listeners (active-leaf-change, layout-change) never\r\nre-fire for an already-active pinned canvas, leaving the prototype\r\nunpatched and frontmatter updates silently broken.\r\n\r\nFix: add onLayoutReady() as the primary patching trigger in both\r\nregisterCanvasAutoLink() and registerCanvasNodeAutoHeightPatcher(),\r\nmirroring the pattern already used in patchCanvasNodeMenu(). Also add\r\ndouble-patch guards (canvasPatched flag and this.uninstaller check) to\r\nprevent wrapping the prototype more than once when multiple callbacks fire.",
      "downloadCount": 59,
      "draft": false,
      "name": "1.0.22-beta",
